<h2>Using the PoiXson Yum Repository</h2>

<p>This repository is built for compatibility with CentOS and Fedora. You may also download the RPM files for manual installation on any OS which supports RPM. Additional file formats for these packages can be found at <a href="http://dl.poixson.com/">http://dl.poixson.com/</a></p>

<p>You may run the following command to install the pxn repo into your system. This will allow you to easily and quickly install packages, and receive automatic updates.</p>

<pre>
<textarea style="width: 450px; height: 50px;" onfocus="this.select();" onmouseup="return false;" ondblclick="return false;" ondrag="return false;">yum install http://yum.poixson.com/latest.rpm</textarea>
</pre>

